  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-31 01:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Ticks Up + BTC Bounce to $67.2K\n\n**Task:** Check F&G trend, shadow tracker data, overnight market.\n\n**F&G Index:** 8\u219211 (+3). First uptick in 3 days. Still Extreme Fear. 7-day range 8-14, avg 11. Our V4.1 edge modifier (+0.05) active continuously for 7+ days. No change needed.\n\n**Shadow Tracker:** 8 entries in 25 min (cron working). 6 YES_ONLY_FILTER, 1 BIAS_TOO_WEAK, 1 WOULD_TRADE_YES (1h UTC, bias -26.8). Outcome pending. Data collection working correctly.\n\n**BTC Rally: $66,700 \u2192 $67,215 (+$500, +0.8%)**\n- Overnight bounce from daily low of $66,262\n- Now $379 above HL BTC LONG entry ($66,836) \u2192 position profitable\n- If this holds \u2192 11h regime likely RANGE (BTC needs to be ranging, not trending)\n- Good setup for tomorrow morning session\n\n**HL Position Impact:**\n- BTC LONG: now profitable (~+$1.30 at 3x on $109 notional)\n- ETH SHORT: still profitable (+$1.50 if ETH didn't move proportionally)\n- SOL LONG: likely improving with BTC correlation\n\n## 2026-03-31 00:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Shadow Trade Tracker V2: Excluded Hours Data Collection\n\n**Task:** Build automated shadow trade tracker for V5 hour optimization.\n\n**Built:** `scripts/shadow-trade-tracker-v2.sh`\n- Runs every 5 min via cron (self-skips during active hours 11/12/19/20)\n- Simulates V4.1 filter logic: bias thresholds, YES-only, dead zone\n- For would-trade signals: spawns background outcome check 5 min later\n- Outputs JSONL to `logs/shadow-trades-v2.jsonl` with entry + outcome pairs\n- Tracks: ho",
